19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,942
<i>As war
continues to fracture the galaxy,</i>

20
00:00:20,983 --> 00:00:24,111
<i>planets become pawns
in a dangerous chess game.</i>

21
00:00:24,237 --> 00:00:26,239
<i>One planet in peril is Naboo,</i>

22
00:00:26,531 --> 00:00:29,659
<i>where suffering and civil unrest
threaten once-friendly relations</i>

23
00:00:29,742 --> 00:00:33,454
<i>between the people on the surface
and the underwater-dwelling Gungans.</i>

24
00:00:33,704 --> 00:00:37,416
<i>Rumors that the Gungans plan to aid
the Separatists in an attack on Theed</i>

25
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,544
<i>force senator Padmé Amidala home,</i>

26
00:00:39,627 --> 00:00:42,880
<i>accompanied by Jedi General
Anakin Skywalker.</i>

27
00:00:55,434 --> 00:00:57,478
Jar Jar, do you read me? It's Anakin.

28
00:00:57,770 --> 00:01:00,565
We need you to meet us on the surface
of Lake Paonga immediately.

29
00:01:00,731 --> 00:01:02,316
<i>Okie day, mui palo.</i>

30
00:01:02,525 --> 00:01:04,318
<i>There's bombad trouble down here.</i>

31
00:01:04,485 --> 00:01:06,988
We know.
That's why we need to talk to you.

32
00:01:22,503 --> 00:01:25,715
Oh, boy. Mesa must stop
zipping to the surface.

33
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,758
Ears go boomba some day.

34
00:01:31,387 --> 00:01:34,307
What's going on, Jar Jar?
We're hearing disturbing rumors.

35
00:01:34,682 --> 00:01:37,018
Is Boss Lyonie calling
for a march on Theed?

36
00:01:37,059 --> 00:01:41,022
Oh, yes, my lady.
He give mui fiery speeches,

37
00:01:41,188 --> 00:01:43,024
blaming Naboo for everything.

38
00:01:43,357 --> 00:01:45,192
Mesa say it couldn't be true.

39
00:01:45,401 --> 00:01:46,861
Of course, it's not.

40
00:01:47,028 --> 00:01:48,696
We need to talk to him, Jar Jar.

41
00:02:11,260 --> 00:02:17,892
For centuries the Nabooians have treated
you like second-class citizens.

42
00:02:18,309 --> 00:02:20,061
No more!

43
00:02:20,561 --> 00:02:26,359
There's moments in history
when change is necessary.

44
00:02:26,984 --> 00:02:31,322
Are you going to take
what is rightfully ours?

45
00:02:35,409 --> 00:02:40,039
This mui mui bad. Don't worry, General,
mesa friends can help.

46
00:02:40,498 --> 00:02:42,583
Mesa hope so, Jar Jar.

47
00:02:54,428 --> 00:02:55,763
Be quick.

48
00:02:58,766 --> 00:03:04,939
Young Senator Amidala, if you here
to talk mesa out of marching on Theed,

49
00:03:05,022 --> 00:03:06,565
you wasting time.

50
00:03:06,941 --> 00:03:10,653
With all due respect,
your course of action is based on lies.

51
00:03:10,986 --> 00:03:12,947
You must make your warriors stand down.

52
00:03:13,364 --> 00:03:16,992
Mesa different now! Mesa enlightened!

53
00:03:17,493 --> 00:03:19,912
See? Acting loconut.

54
00:03:19,954 --> 00:03:22,039
He seems possessed,
if you ask me.

55
00:03:22,415 --> 00:03:25,292
Or under someone's influence.

56
00:03:25,543 --> 00:03:28,754
Stop whispering and go, be gone.

57
00:03:30,506 --> 00:03:31,674
The necklace!

58
00:03:36,554 --> 00:03:38,472
What's happening?

59
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,767
Binks? Who are they?

60
00:03:42,226 --> 00:03:45,688
Who are we? Boss Lyonie,
don't you remember anything?

61
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,898
Who gave you this necklace, Your Majesty?

62
00:03:48,232 --> 00:03:51,318
Minister Rish Loo, he given it to me.

63
00:03:51,402 --> 00:03:55,865
He telling me it make me
bombad leader, very powerful.

64
00:03:56,532 --> 00:04:00,286
They say Rish Loo know ancient
Gungan mystical power.

65
00:04:00,494 --> 00:04:02,204
Mind over matter.

66
00:04:02,496 --> 00:04:04,123
But he only use it for good.

67
00:04:04,415 --> 00:04:05,666
Until now, you mean.

68
00:04:13,048 --> 00:04:17,052
Events, they're proceeding
as planned, Count.

69
00:04:17,136 --> 00:04:18,220
<i>Very good.</i>

70
00:04:18,304 --> 00:04:23,517
Mesa able to persuade the officers
to allowing the Separatist army

71
00:04:23,684 --> 00:04:26,896
easy access into Naboo.

72
00:04:27,188 --> 00:04:30,691
<i>You're doing the right thing
for your people, Minister Loo.</i>

73
00:04:34,695 --> 00:04:36,447
Let mesa go in alone.

74
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:38,407
We'll be right outside.

75
00:04:41,202 --> 00:04:45,331
And mesa counsel will be rewarded
in yo us a new order?

76
00:04:45,706 --> 00:04:47,708
<i>You will be most influential.</i>

77
00:04:49,168 --> 00:04:50,878
Someone is coming.

78
00:04:56,008 --> 00:05:01,180
Why it's Boss Lyonie!
What do mesa owe the pleasure?

79
00:05:01,722 --> 00:05:03,349
You tricked me, Rish Loo.

80
00:05:03,724 --> 00:05:06,560
-Mesa don't...
-You used magical powers

81
00:05:06,644 --> 00:05:08,938
to manipulate mesa head-thoughts.

82
00:05:09,021 --> 00:05:12,233
Mesa never attack the surface-dwelling
brothers and sisters

83
00:05:12,274 --> 00:05:14,318
unless you clouded mesa head.

84
00:05:14,401 --> 00:05:17,238
You not thinking clearly, bombad leader.

85
00:05:17,696 --> 00:05:20,324
Where's the necklace mesa given you?

86
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:23,911
It's destroyed. You not control me no more.

87
00:05:24,245 --> 00:05:27,122
You mistaken, king fool.

88
00:05:27,706 --> 00:05:29,917
Something's wrong, we better get up there.

89
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:36,298
Boss Lyonie, don't listen to him!

90
00:05:36,674 --> 00:05:37,925
You get them!

91
00:06:15,045 --> 00:06:16,714
-Check on Boss Lyonie.
-Ani!

92
00:06:41,906 --> 00:06:44,241
This is mui upsetting, my lady.

93
00:06:44,325 --> 00:06:45,618
I know, Jar Jar.

94
00:06:45,659 --> 00:06:46,744
How is he?

95
00:06:46,827 --> 00:06:50,039
The bandages have stopped the bleeding,
but he's unconscious.

96
00:06:50,122 --> 00:06:51,457
The Gungans are still gathered

97
00:06:51,498 --> 00:06:53,000
and poised to march on Theed.

98
00:06:53,417 --> 00:06:55,836
Boss Lyonie never got a chance
to call off the invasion.

99
00:06:56,211 --> 00:06:58,005
And it's almost dusk.

100
00:06:58,172 --> 00:07:00,132
Jar Jar, you're a senator,

101
00:07:00,174 --> 00:07:02,426
you have to tell them to stand down.
They'll listen to you.

102
00:07:03,052 --> 00:07:04,762
These Gungans are proud.

103
00:07:04,845 --> 00:07:08,557
With the mood at the moment,
mesa the last person they'll listen to now.

104
00:07:09,183 --> 00:07:10,267
Huh.

105
00:07:10,434 --> 00:07:12,227
I don't believe it.

106
00:07:12,353 --> 00:07:14,688
The resemblance is remarkable.

107
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:19,985
Who resembles what?

108
00:07:20,194 --> 00:07:22,363
You. You look just like Boss Lyonie.

109
00:07:22,696 --> 00:07:24,949
I didn't realize it until you put the crown on.

110
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:26,367
This gives me an idea.

111
00:07:27,034 --> 00:07:29,703
Jar Jar, you must put on Lyonie's robes
and keep that crown on.

112
00:07:29,912 --> 00:07:32,122
Oh, no, no! Mesa can't do that.

113
00:07:32,373 --> 00:07:35,084
You have to if we're going to convince
the Gungan army to stand down.

114
00:07:35,209 --> 00:07:37,002
But they never listen to mesa.

115
00:07:37,086 --> 00:07:40,214
Maybe not,
but they will listen to Boss Lyonie.

116
00:07:40,381 --> 00:07:41,715
But we all don't look alike!

117
00:07:44,885 --> 00:07:48,722
This a sad day for all Gungans.

118
00:07:49,390 --> 00:07:54,687
Our beloved leader, Boss Lyonie, is dead.

119
00:07:57,356 --> 00:08:00,401
We must honor his last order

120
00:08:00,484 --> 00:08:05,572
and prepare for our attack
against the Naboo.

121
00:08:06,156 --> 00:08:11,829
We march with the Separatist
droid army on Theed!

122
00:08:12,162 --> 00:08:14,415
Death to the Naboo!

123
00:08:20,462 --> 00:08:22,798
This bad. This very bad.

124
00:08:23,048 --> 00:08:25,092
Get up there and stop the attack.

125
00:08:25,259 --> 00:08:26,301
Er...

126
00:08:26,385 --> 00:08:27,803
Mesa can't do it.

127
00:08:27,886 --> 00:08:32,141
You can't, but Boss Lyonie can.
Now get out there.

128
00:08:34,685 --> 00:08:38,480
It's Boss Lyonie. He's alive.

129
00:08:42,359 --> 00:08:43,652
Say something.

130
00:08:44,403 --> 00:08:45,779
I...

131
00:08:47,406 --> 00:08:49,783
He is alive, he is.

132
00:08:51,785 --> 00:08:54,955
Mesa...
Mesa fellow Gungans.

133
00:08:56,248 --> 00:09:01,128
Mesa made terrible mistake
ordering march on Theed.

134
00:09:01,670 --> 00:09:04,631
We canceling our attack.

135
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,884
It is Boss Lyonie.

136
00:09:07,092 --> 00:09:08,135
It's working.

137
00:09:08,177 --> 00:09:12,848
Rish Loo manipulated mesa head-thoughts

138
00:09:13,098 --> 00:09:15,851
with lies and misinformation.

139
00:09:16,185 --> 00:09:18,312
He's the real enemy.

140
00:09:22,858 --> 00:09:25,027
No, no!

141
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:39,541
Good work, now try not to mess this up,
Boss Lyonie.

142
00:09:57,017 --> 00:09:59,311
Battle droids? What they doing here?

143
00:09:59,812 --> 00:10:03,649
They think we still allies
because of Rish Loo.

144
00:10:04,483 --> 00:10:08,362
Our General wishes to speak with you
about the canceled attack.

145
00:10:08,779 --> 00:10:10,906
-Jar Jar?
-No, Lyonie.

146
00:10:11,323 --> 00:10:13,033
Mesa Boss Lyonie.

147
00:10:13,617 --> 00:10:15,369
Mesa talk to the General.

148
00:10:15,536 --> 00:10:16,870
Follow me.

149
00:10:31,885 --> 00:10:37,641
Come in, Minister Lyonie.
Let's sit down and have a talk.

150
00:10:42,062 --> 00:10:45,399
Has this seat been taken? Here.

151
00:10:48,443 --> 00:10:49,570
So...

152
00:10:50,904 --> 00:10:51,989
So...

153
00:10:52,573 --> 00:10:58,078
I hear you have decided not to aid
our attack on the Naboo.

154
00:11:01,957 --> 00:11:03,959
Oh, yes. Yes.

155
00:11:04,084 --> 00:11:08,338
We must put end to unfortunate,
unfortunate bang-bang conflict.

156
00:11:09,006 --> 00:11:14,136
It was a great effort and cost
for me to bring my armies here.

157
00:11:14,469 --> 00:11:17,890
Mesa sorry that Boss...

158
00:11:18,015 --> 00:11:19,683
Excuse me. Ahem.

159
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:23,020
Mesa was receiving mui bad advice.

160
00:11:23,562 --> 00:11:27,524
If you won't attack the Naboo, I will.

161
00:11:28,692 --> 00:11:31,445
Hold that thought. General Tarpals!

162
00:11:32,070 --> 00:11:33,488
Yes, Boss?

163
00:11:34,156 --> 00:11:36,783
You need to do that.

164
00:11:37,117 --> 00:11:40,787
That thing, that big troop thing.

165
00:11:41,121 --> 00:11:42,873
What did you just say?

166
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:47,461
Go, go.

167
00:11:48,378 --> 00:11:53,884
Mesa... Mesa just telling General that we
must make the immediate arrangement

168
00:11:54,218 --> 00:11:57,012
for a Gungan-Separatist attack.

169
00:12:01,683 --> 00:12:05,229
Senator, mesa has urgent message
from Boss Lyonie.

170
00:12:05,562 --> 00:12:08,440
He say General Grievous is here.

171
00:12:08,774 --> 00:12:10,901
<i>Grievous is here? Where's Anakin?</i>

172
00:12:11,151 --> 00:12:12,986
He's chasing Rish Loo.

173
00:12:13,153 --> 00:12:17,032
<i>General Tarpals, listen to me,
you must capture Grievous.</i>

174
00:12:17,449 --> 00:12:20,869
But how?
There's too many droids helping him.

175
00:12:21,328 --> 00:12:23,789
<i>The droid commander still thinks
you're on the same side,</i>

176
00:12:24,498 --> 00:12:29,044
<i>have the droids shut down, then attack.
It's the only way.</i>

177
00:12:29,503 --> 00:12:34,967
Grievous is a bombad warrior,
but we shall do as you say.

178
00:12:35,509 --> 00:12:40,806
I always be believing in the friendship
between Gungans and the Naboo.

179
00:12:41,265 --> 00:12:42,349
<i>Thank you, General.</i>

180
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:19,303
Oh!

181
00:13:20,512 --> 00:13:22,472
What are we waiting for?

182
00:13:22,556 --> 00:13:25,684
Hmm. Planning attack take time.

183
00:13:26,476 --> 00:13:29,896
You are a man of few words, Boss Lyonie.

184
00:13:29,938 --> 00:13:32,941
Well, mesa more of a deep thinker.

185
00:13:35,694 --> 00:13:38,030
You are not Boss Lyonie.

186
00:13:41,325 --> 00:13:45,329
You have no idea of the power
within my grasp.

187
00:13:55,589 --> 00:13:56,673
Uh-oh!

188
00:13:57,883 --> 00:13:58,925
Huh?

189
00:13:59,176 --> 00:14:02,262
You army is shut down, General.

190
00:14:08,602 --> 00:14:11,104
Mesa suggest you surrender.

191
00:14:18,111 --> 00:14:20,072
You can't be serious?

192
00:14:46,139 --> 00:14:48,850
How does it feel to die?

193
00:14:49,476 --> 00:14:51,269
Not die.

194
00:14:52,896 --> 00:14:54,898
Sacrifice.

195
00:14:57,859 --> 00:14:59,319
Jar Jar, now!

196
00:15:12,332 --> 00:15:14,084
Huh?

197
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:42,904
<i>This turn of events is unfortunate.</i>

198
00:15:43,530 --> 00:15:48,034
<i>General Grievous is a critical part of my
plan for the Clone Wars.</i>

199
00:15:48,452 --> 00:15:50,829
<i>He must not remain captive.</i>

200
00:15:51,371 --> 00:15:53,039
What is to be done, my lord?

201
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:59,880
<i>You must lure Skywalker into a trap,
then negotiate a prisoner exchange.</i>

202
00:16:00,547 --> 00:16:04,384
How can you be certain the Republic
will trade Grievous for Skywalker?

203
00:16:04,718 --> 00:16:10,265
<i>I have no doubt Senator Amidala
will gladly agree to your terms.</i>

204
00:16:11,057 --> 00:16:12,476
As you wish, my lord.

205
00:16:16,188 --> 00:16:18,231
-Rish Loo.
<i>-Yes, Count?</i>

206
00:16:19,065 --> 00:16:21,193
I am at your secret laboratory.

207
00:16:21,234 --> 00:16:26,239
Meet me here and leave enough of a trail
for Skywalker to follow you.

208
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:29,242
I have a surprise waiting for him.

209
00:16:51,139 --> 00:16:55,310
Master, I have done what you asked.

210
00:16:55,769 --> 00:16:57,771
Skywalker is here.

211
00:16:58,188 --> 00:17:03,026
Young Master Skywalker,
you're nothing if not relentless.

212
00:17:03,235 --> 00:17:05,612
-What a surprise.
-Dooku.

213
00:17:06,404 --> 00:17:07,948
You're a fool, Rish Loo.

214
00:17:20,043 --> 00:17:21,670
Why bring the war to Naboo?

215
00:17:21,753 --> 00:17:23,547
How quickly you forget.

216
00:17:24,172 --> 00:17:27,300
After all, the war started here years ago.

217
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:29,386
You were a part of that first battle?

218
00:17:29,844 --> 00:17:33,890
The Sith control everything,
you just don't know it.

219
00:19:10,070 --> 00:19:13,073
Where's Ani? He been gone mui long time.

220
00:19:13,365 --> 00:19:14,866
I'm not sure, Jar Jar.

221
00:19:16,242 --> 00:19:17,577
Anakin!

222
00:19:19,412 --> 00:19:22,290
Senator Amidala, we meet again.

223
00:19:22,582 --> 00:19:27,295
I must regretfully inform you
that young Skywalker has been detained.

224
00:19:27,754 --> 00:19:30,215
<i>What have you done with Anakin?</i>

225
00:19:30,423 --> 00:19:33,760
Now, now, Senator,
let's not become emotional.

226
00:19:34,094 --> 00:19:35,345
What do you want, Dooku?

227
00:19:35,553 --> 00:19:37,013
<i>I'm glad you asked.</i>

228
00:19:37,597 --> 00:19:41,184
I could be persuaded
to return Skywalker to you

229
00:19:41,267 --> 00:19:44,771
in exchange for General Grievous.

230
00:19:47,107 --> 00:19:49,609
I can't do that. I'm sorry.

231
00:19:50,151 --> 00:19:51,778
You soon will be.

232
00:19:56,157 --> 00:19:59,202
<i>Stop! You cannot torture a prisoner.</i>

233
00:19:59,577 --> 00:20:02,247
Torture? I don't know what you mean.

234
00:20:03,415 --> 00:20:06,000
I'll give you an hour
to consider my proposition.

235
00:20:06,084 --> 00:20:09,003
I'm sure you will make the right choice.

236
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:12,006
You have to trade with him.

237
00:20:12,507 --> 00:20:14,134
I can't, Jar Jar.

238
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:17,137
With Grievous captured,
we could win the war.

239
00:20:17,512 --> 00:20:21,391
But, Padmé, he's our friend.

240
00:20:21,683 --> 00:20:24,477
I know. I know, Jar Jar.

241
00:20:24,894 --> 00:20:26,646
Mesa think you have to deal.

242
00:20:27,272 --> 00:20:30,358
You should listen to Binks, he's right.

243
00:20:53,089 --> 00:20:54,841
Release the General.

244
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:24,287
Padmé, I'm sorry.

245
00:21:24,621 --> 00:21:25,705
Shh.

246
00:21:25,789 --> 00:21:27,207
It's all right, Ani.

247
00:21:40,053 --> 00:21:43,598
Binks, you been bombad leader
in my place.

248
00:21:43,681 --> 00:21:47,811
This a second time you stopping war
between us and the Naboo.

249
00:21:48,228 --> 00:21:50,396
And we are grateful, Senator Binks.

250
00:21:50,814 --> 00:21:52,273
Mesa doing my best.

251
00:21:52,297 --> 00:21:57,297
http://hiqve.com/

